headline: Libya’s NOC Lifts Output, Eyes 2 Million bpd by 2028
summary: Libya’s National Oil Corporation (NOC) said on August 19 that it produced over 1.38 million barrels of crude in the prior 24 hours, plus ~50,000 b/d of condensate and 2.48 bcf of natural gas.
